{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm a storyteller."},{"time":2000,"text":"That's what I do in life -- telling stories,"},{"time":4000,"text":"writing novels --"},{"time":6000,"text":"and today I would like to tell you a few stories"},{"time":8000,"text":"about the art of storytelling"},{"time":10000,"text":"and also some supernatural creatures"},{"time":12000,"text":"called the djinni."},{"time":14000,"text":"But before I go there, please allow me to share with you"},{"time":17000,"text":"glimpses of my personal story."},{"time":19000,"text":"I will do so with the help of words, of course,"},{"time":22000,"text":"but also a geometrical shape, the circle,"},{"time":25000,"text":"so throughout my talk,"},{"time":27000,"text":"you will come across several circles."}]},{"cues":[{"time":30000,"text":"I was born in Strasbourg, France"},{"time":33000,"text":"to Turkish parents."},{"time":35000,"text":"Shortly after, my parents got separated,"},{"time":37000,"text":"and I came to Turkey with my mom."},{"time":39000,"text":"From then on, I was raised"},{"time":41000,"text":"as a single child by a single mother."},{"time":43000,"text":"Now in the early 1970s, in Ankara,"},{"time":45000,"text":"that was a bit unusual."},{"time":47000,"text":"Our neighborhood was full of large families,"},{"time":49000,"text":"where fathers were the heads of households,"},{"time":52000,"text":"so I grew up seeing my mother as a divorcee"},{"time":55000,"text":"in a patriarchal environment."},{"time":57000,"text":"In fact, I grew up observing"},{"time":59000,"text":"two different kinds of womanhood."},{"time":61000,"text":"On the one hand was my mother,"},{"time":63000,"text":"a well-educated, secular, modern, westernized, Turkish woman."},{"time":66000,"text":"On the other hand was my grandmother,"},{"time":68000,"text":"who also took care of me"},{"time":70000,"text":"and was more spiritual, less educated"},{"time":73000,"text":"and definitely less rational."},{"time":75000,"text":"This was a woman who read coffee grounds to see the future"},{"time":78000,"text":"and melted lead into mysterious shapes"},{"time":80000,"text":"to fend off the evil eye."}]},{"cues":[{"time":83000,"text":"Many people visited my grandmother,"},{"time":85000,"text":"people with severe acne on their faces"},{"time":87000,"text":"or warts on their hands."},{"time":90000,"text":"Each time, my grandmother would utter some words in Arabic,"},{"time":93000,"text":"take a red apple and stab it"},{"time":95000,"text":"with as many rose thorns"},{"time":97000,"text":"as the number of warts she wanted to remove."},{"time":100000,"text":"Then one by one, she would"},{"time":102000,"text":"encircle these thorns with dark ink."},{"time":105000,"text":"A week later, the patient would come back"},{"time":107000,"text":"for a follow-up examination."},{"time":109000,"text":"Now, I'm aware that I should not be saying such things"},{"time":112000,"text":"in front of an audience of scholars and scientists,"},{"time":115000,"text":"but the truth is, of all the people"},{"time":117000,"text":"who visited my grandmother for their skin conditions,"},{"time":120000,"text":"I did not see anyone go back"},{"time":122000,"text":"unhappy or unhealed."},{"time":125000,"text":"I asked her how she did this. Was it the power of praying?"},{"time":128000,"text":"In response she said, \"Yes, praying is effective,"},{"time":131000,"text":"but also beware of the power of circles.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":134000,"text":"From her, I learned, amongst many other things,"},{"time":137000,"text":"one very precious lesson --"},{"time":139000,"text":"that if you want to destroy something in this life,"},{"time":141000,"text":"be it an acne, a blemish"},{"time":143000,"text":"or the human soul,"},{"time":145000,"text":"all you need to do is to surround it with thick walls."},{"time":148000,"text":"It will dry up inside."},{"time":150000,"text":"Now we all live in some kind of a social and cultural circle."},{"time":153000,"text":"We all do."},{"time":155000,"text":"We're born into a certain family, nation, class."},{"time":158000,"text":"But if we have no connection whatsoever"},{"time":161000,"text":"with the worlds beyond the one we take for granted,"},{"time":163000,"text":"then we too run the risk"},{"time":165000,"text":"of drying up inside."},{"time":167000,"text":"Our imagination might shrink;"},{"time":169000,"text":"our hearts might dwindle,"},{"time":171000,"text":"and our humanness might wither"},{"time":173000,"text":"if we stay for too long"},{"time":175000,"text":"inside our cultural cocoons."},{"time":177000,"text":"Our friends, neighbors, colleagues, family --"},{"time":180000,"text":"if all the people in our inner circle resemble us,"},{"time":182000,"text":"it means we are surrounded"},{"time":184000,"text":"with our mirror image."}]},{"cues":[{"time":186000,"text":"Now one other thing women like my grandma do in Turkey"},{"time":189000,"text":"is to cover mirrors with velvet"},{"time":191000,"text":"or to hang them on the walls with their backs facing out."},{"time":194000,"text":"It's an old Eastern tradition"},{"time":196000,"text":"based on the knowledge that it's not healthy"},{"time":198000,"text":"for a human being to spend too much time"},{"time":201000,"text":"staring at his own reflection."},{"time":203000,"text":"Ironically, [living in] communities of the like-minded"},{"time":206000,"text":"is one of the greatest dangers"},{"time":208000,"text":"of today's globalized world."},{"time":210000,"text":"And it's happening everywhere,"},{"time":212000,"text":"among liberals and conservatives,"},{"time":214000,"text":"agnostics and believers, the rich and the poor,"},{"time":216000,"text":"East and West alike."},{"time":218000,"text":"We tend to form clusters"},{"time":220000,"text":"based on similarity,"},{"time":222000,"text":"and then we produce stereotypes"},{"time":224000,"text":"about other clusters of people."},{"time":226000,"text":"In my opinion, one way of transcending"},{"time":228000,"text":"these cultural ghettos"},{"time":230000,"text":"is through the art of storytelling."},{"time":232000,"text":"Stories cannot demolish frontiers,"},{"time":235000,"text":"but they can punch holes in our mental walls."},{"time":238000,"text":"And through those holes, we can get a glimpse of the other,"},{"time":241000,"text":"and sometimes even like what we see."}]},{"cues":[{"time":244000,"text":"I started writing fiction at the age of eight."},{"time":247000,"text":"My mother came home one day with a turquoise notebook"},{"time":250000,"text":"and asked me if I'd be interested in keeping a personal journal."},{"time":253000,"text":"In retrospect, I think she was slightly worried"},{"time":255000,"text":"about my sanity."},{"time":257000,"text":"I was constantly telling stories at home, which was good,"},{"time":260000,"text":"except I told this to imaginary friends around me,"},{"time":262000,"text":"which was not so good."},{"time":264000,"text":"I was an introverted child,"},{"time":266000,"text":"to the point of communicating with colored crayons"},{"time":269000,"text":"and apologizing to objects"},{"time":271000,"text":"when I bumped into them,"},{"time":273000,"text":"so my mother thought it might do me good"},{"time":275000,"text":"to write down my day-to-day experiences"},{"time":277000,"text":"and emotions."},{"time":279000,"text":"What she didn't know was that I thought my life was terribly boring,"},{"time":282000,"text":"and the last thing I wanted to do"},{"time":284000,"text":"was to write about myself."},{"time":286000,"text":"Instead, I began to write about people other than me"},{"time":289000,"text":"and things that never really happened."},{"time":291000,"text":"And thus began my life-long passion"},{"time":293000,"text":"for writing fiction."},{"time":295000,"text":"So from the very beginning, fiction for me"},{"time":298000,"text":"was less of an autobiographical manifestation"},{"time":301000,"text":"than a transcendental journey"},{"time":303000,"text":"into other lives, other possibilities."},{"time":305000,"text":"And please bear with me:"},{"time":307000,"text":"I'll draw a circle and come back to this point."}]},{"cues":[{"time":310000,"text":"Now one other thing happened around this same time."},{"time":312000,"text":"My mother became a diplomat."},{"time":314000,"text":"So from this small, superstitious,"},{"time":316000,"text":"middle-class neighborhood of my grandmother,"},{"time":319000,"text":"I was zoomed into this"},{"time":321000,"text":"posh, international school [in Madrid],"},{"time":323000,"text":"where I was the only Turk."},{"time":325000,"text":"It was here that I had my first encounter"},{"time":327000,"text":"with what I call the \"representative foreigner.\""},{"time":330000,"text":"In our classroom, there were children from all nationalities,"},{"time":333000,"text":"yet this diversity did not necessarily lead"},{"time":336000,"text":"to a cosmopolitan, egalitarian"},{"time":339000,"text":"classroom democracy."},{"time":341000,"text":"Instead, it generated an atmosphere"},{"time":343000,"text":"in which each child was seen --"},{"time":345000,"text":"not as an individual on his own,"},{"time":347000,"text":"but as the representative of something larger."},{"time":350000,"text":"We were like a miniature United Nations, which was fun,"},{"time":353000,"text":"except whenever something negative,"},{"time":355000,"text":"with regards to a nation"},{"time":357000,"text":"or a religion, took place."},{"time":359000,"text":"The child who represented it was mocked,"},{"time":362000,"text":"ridiculed and bullied endlessly."},{"time":365000,"text":"And I should know, because during the time I attended that school,"},{"time":368000,"text":"a military takeover happened in my country,"},{"time":371000,"text":"a gunman of my nationality nearly killed the Pope,"},{"time":374000,"text":"and Turkey got zero points in [the] Eurovision Song Contest."},{"time":377000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":379000,"text":"I skipped school often and dreamed of becoming a sailor"},{"time":381000,"text":"during those days."},{"time":383000,"text":"I also had my first taste"},{"time":385000,"text":"of cultural stereotypes there."},{"time":387000,"text":"The other children asked me about the movie"},{"time":389000,"text":"\"Midnight Express,\" which I had not seen;"},{"time":391000,"text":"they inquired how many cigarettes a day I smoked,"},{"time":394000,"text":"because they thought all Turks were heavy smokers,"},{"time":397000,"text":"and they wondered at what age"},{"time":399000,"text":"I would start covering my hair."},{"time":401000,"text":"I came to learn that these were"},{"time":403000,"text":"the three main stereotypes about my country:"},{"time":405000,"text":"politics, cigarettes"},{"time":407000,"text":"and the veil."},{"time":409000,"text":"After Spain, we went to Jordan, Germany"},{"time":411000,"text":"and Ankara again."},{"time":413000,"text":"Everywhere I went, I felt like"},{"time":415000,"text":"my imagination was the only suitcase"},{"time":417000,"text":"I could take with me."},{"time":419000,"text":"Stories gave me a sense of center,"},{"time":421000,"text":"continuity and coherence,"},{"time":423000,"text":"the three big Cs that I otherwise lacked."}]},{"cues":[{"time":426000,"text":"In my mid-twenties, I moved to Istanbul,"},{"time":428000,"text":"the city I adore."},{"time":430000,"text":"I lived in a very vibrant, diverse neighborhood"},{"time":433000,"text":"where I wrote several of my novels."},{"time":435000,"text":"I was in Istanbul when the earthquake hit"},{"time":437000,"text":"in 1999."},{"time":439000,"text":"When I ran out of the building at three in the morning,"},{"time":442000,"text":"I saw something that stopped me in my tracks."},{"time":445000,"text":"There was the local grocer there --"},{"time":447000,"text":"a grumpy, old man who didn't sell alcohol"},{"time":449000,"text":"and didn't speak to marginals."},{"time":451000,"text":"He was sitting next to a transvestite"},{"time":454000,"text":"with a long black wig"},{"time":456000,"text":"and mascara running down her cheeks."},{"time":458000,"text":"I watched the man open a pack of cigarettes"},{"time":460000,"text":"with trembling hands"},{"time":462000,"text":"and offer one to her,"},{"time":464000,"text":"and that is the image of the night of the earthquake"},{"time":466000,"text":"in my mind today --"},{"time":468000,"text":"a conservative grocer and a crying transvestite"},{"time":471000,"text":"smoking together on the sidewalk."},{"time":473000,"text":"In the face of death and destruction,"},{"time":476000,"text":"our mundane differences evaporated,"},{"time":478000,"text":"and we all became one"},{"time":480000,"text":"even if for a few hours."},{"time":482000,"text":"But I've always believed that stories, too, have a similar effect on us."},{"time":485000,"text":"I'm not saying that fiction has the magnitude of an earthquake,"},{"time":488000,"text":"but when we are reading a good novel,"},{"time":490000,"text":"we leave our small, cozy apartments behind,"},{"time":493000,"text":"go out into the night alone"},{"time":495000,"text":"and start getting to know people we had never met before"},{"time":498000,"text":"and perhaps had even been biased against."}]},{"cues":[{"time":501000,"text":"Shortly after, I went"},{"time":503000,"text":"to a women's college in Boston, then Michigan."},{"time":506000,"text":"I experienced this, not so much as a geographical shift,"},{"time":509000,"text":"as a linguistic one."},{"time":511000,"text":"I started writing fiction in English."},{"time":513000,"text":"I'm not an immigrant, refugee or exile --"},{"time":515000,"text":"they ask me why I do this --"},{"time":517000,"text":"but the commute between languages"},{"time":519000,"text":"gives me the chance to recreate myself."},{"time":522000,"text":"I love writing in Turkish,"},{"time":524000,"text":"which to me is very poetic and very emotional,"},{"time":527000,"text":"and I love writing in English, which to me"},{"time":529000,"text":"is very mathematical and cerebral."},{"time":531000,"text":"So I feel connected to each language in a different way."},{"time":534000,"text":"For me, like millions of other people"},{"time":536000,"text":"around the world today,"},{"time":538000,"text":"English is an acquired language."},{"time":540000,"text":"When you're a latecomer to a language,"},{"time":542000,"text":"what happens is you live there"},{"time":545000,"text":"with a continuous"},{"time":547000,"text":"and perpetual frustration."},{"time":549000,"text":"As latecomers, we always want to say more, you know,"},{"time":551000,"text":"crack better jokes, say better things,"},{"time":554000,"text":"but we end up saying less"},{"time":556000,"text":"because there's a gap between the mind and the tongue."},{"time":558000,"text":"And that gap is very intimidating."},{"time":561000,"text":"But if we manage not to be frightened by it,"},{"time":563000,"text":"it's also stimulating."},{"time":565000,"text":"And this is what I discovered in Boston --"},{"time":567000,"text":"that frustration was very stimulating."}]},{"cues":[{"time":570000,"text":"At this stage, my grandmother,"},{"time":571000,"text":"who had been watching the course of my life"},{"time":573000,"text":"with increasing anxiety,"},{"time":575000,"text":"started to include in her daily prayers"},{"time":577000,"text":"that I urgently get married"},{"time":579000,"text":"so that I could settle down once and for all."},{"time":582000,"text":"And because God loves her, I did get married."},{"time":585000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":587000,"text":"But instead of settling down,"},{"time":589000,"text":"I went to Arizona."},{"time":591000,"text":"And since my husband is in Istanbul,"},{"time":593000,"text":"I started commuting between Arizona and Istanbul --"},{"time":596000,"text":"the two places on the surface of earth"},{"time":598000,"text":"that couldn't be more different."},{"time":600000,"text":"I guess one part of me has always been a nomad,"},{"time":603000,"text":"physically and spiritually."},{"time":605000,"text":"Stories accompany me,"},{"time":607000,"text":"keeping my pieces and memories together,"},{"time":609000,"text":"like an existential glue."}]},{"cues":[{"time":611000,"text":"Yet as much as I love stories,"},{"time":613000,"text":"recently, I've also begun to think"},{"time":616000,"text":"that they lose their magic"},{"time":618000,"text":"if and when a story is seen as more than a story."},{"time":621000,"text":"And this is a subject that I would love"},{"time":623000,"text":"to think about together."},{"time":625000,"text":"When my first novel written in English came out in America,"},{"time":628000,"text":"I heard an interesting remark from a literary critic."},{"time":631000,"text":"\"I liked your book,\" he said, \"but I wish you had written it differently.\""},{"time":634000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":638000,"text":"I asked him what he meant by that."},{"time":640000,"text":"He said, \"Well, look at it. There's so many"},{"time":642000,"text":"Spanish, American, Hispanic characters in it,"},{"time":644000,"text":"but there's only one Turkish character and it's a man.\""},{"time":647000,"text":"Now the novel took place on a university campus in Boston,"},{"time":650000,"text":"so to me, it was normal"},{"time":652000,"text":"that there be more international characters in it"},{"time":654000,"text":"than Turkish characters,"},{"time":656000,"text":"but I understood what my critic was looking for."},{"time":658000,"text":"And I also understood that I"},{"time":660000,"text":"would keep disappointing him."},{"time":662000,"text":"He wanted to see the manifestation of my identity."},{"time":665000,"text":"He was looking for a Turkish woman in the book"},{"time":668000,"text":"because I happened to be one."}]},{"cues":[{"time":670000,"text":"We often talk about how stories change the world,"},{"time":673000,"text":"but we should also see how the world of identity politics"},{"time":676000,"text":"affects the way stories"},{"time":678000,"text":"are being circulated,"},{"time":680000,"text":"read and reviewed."},{"time":682000,"text":"Many authors feel this pressure,"},{"time":684000,"text":"but non-Western authors feel it more heavily."},{"time":687000,"text":"If you're a woman writer from the Muslim world, like me,"},{"time":690000,"text":"then you are expected to write"},{"time":692000,"text":"the stories of Muslim women"},{"time":694000,"text":"and, preferably, the unhappy stories"},{"time":696000,"text":"of unhappy Muslim women."},{"time":698000,"text":"You're expected to write"},{"time":700000,"text":"informative, poignant and characteristic stories"},{"time":703000,"text":"and leave the experimental and avant-garde"},{"time":705000,"text":"to your Western colleagues."},{"time":707000,"text":"What I experienced as a child in that school in Madrid"},{"time":710000,"text":"is happening in the literary world today."},{"time":713000,"text":"Writers are not seen"},{"time":715000,"text":"as creative individuals on their own,"},{"time":717000,"text":"but as the representatives"},{"time":719000,"text":"of their respective cultures:"},{"time":721000,"text":"a few authors from China, a few from Turkey,"},{"time":724000,"text":"a few from Nigeria."},{"time":726000,"text":"We're all thought to have something very distinctive,"},{"time":728000,"text":"if not peculiar."}]},{"cues":[{"time":730000,"text":"The writer and commuter James Baldwin"},{"time":733000,"text":"gave an interview in 1984"},{"time":735000,"text":"in which he was repeatedly asked about his homosexuality."},{"time":738000,"text":"When the interviewer tried to pigeonhole him"},{"time":740000,"text":"as a gay writer,"},{"time":742000,"text":"Baldwin stopped and said,"},{"time":744000,"text":"\"But don't you see? There's nothing in me"},{"time":746000,"text":"that is not in everybody else,"},{"time":748000,"text":"and nothing in everybody else"},{"time":750000,"text":"that is not in me.\""},{"time":752000,"text":"When identity politics tries to put labels on us,"},{"time":755000,"text":"it is our freedom of imagination that is in danger."},{"time":758000,"text":"There's a fuzzy category called"},{"time":760000,"text":"multicultural literature"},{"time":762000,"text":"in which all authors from outside the Western world"},{"time":764000,"text":"are lumped together."},{"time":766000,"text":"I never forget my first multicultural reading,"},{"time":768000,"text":"in Harvard Square about 10 years ago."},{"time":771000,"text":"We were three writers, one from the Philippines,"},{"time":774000,"text":"one Turkish and one Indonesian --"},{"time":776000,"text":"like a joke, you know."},{"time":778000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":780000,"text":"And the reason why we were brought together"},{"time":782000,"text":"was not because we shared an artistic style"},{"time":784000,"text":"or a literary taste."},{"time":786000,"text":"It was only because of our passports."},{"time":788000,"text":"Multicultural writers are expected to tell real stories,"},{"time":791000,"text":"not so much the imaginary."},{"time":793000,"text":"A function is attributed to fiction."},{"time":796000,"text":"In this way, not only the writers themselves,"},{"time":798000,"text":"but also their fictional characters"},{"time":801000,"text":"become the representatives of something larger."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804000,"text":"But I must quickly add"},{"time":806000,"text":"that this tendency to see a story"},{"time":808000,"text":"as more than a story"},{"time":810000,"text":"does not solely come from the West."},{"time":812000,"text":"It comes from everywhere."},{"time":814000,"text":"And I experienced this firsthand"},{"time":816000,"text":"when I was put on trial in 2005"},{"time":819000,"text":"for the words my fictional characters uttered in a novel."},{"time":822000,"text":"I had intended to write"},{"time":824000,"text":"a constructive, multi-layered novel"},{"time":827000,"text":"about an Armenian and a Turkish family"},{"time":829000,"text":"through the eyes of women."},{"time":831000,"text":"My micro story became a macro issue"},{"time":834000,"text":"when I was prosecuted."},{"time":836000,"text":"Some people criticized, others praised me"},{"time":838000,"text":"for writing about the Turkish-Armenian conflict."},{"time":841000,"text":"But there were times when I wanted to remind both sides"},{"time":844000,"text":"that this was fiction."},{"time":846000,"text":"It was just a story."},{"time":848000,"text":"And when I say, \"just a story,\""},{"time":850000,"text":"I'm not trying to belittle my work."},{"time":852000,"text":"I want to love and celebrate fiction"},{"time":854000,"text":"for what it is,"},{"time":856000,"text":"not as a means to an end."}]},{"cues":[{"time":858000,"text":"Writers are entitled to their political opinions,"},{"time":860000,"text":"and there are good political novels out there,"},{"time":863000,"text":"but the language of fiction"},{"time":865000,"text":"is not the language of daily politics."},{"time":867000,"text":"Chekhov said,"},{"time":869000,"text":"\"The solution to a problem"},{"time":871000,"text":"and the correct way of posing the question"},{"time":873000,"text":"are two completely separate things."},{"time":876000,"text":"And only the latter is an artist's responsibility.\""},{"time":880000,"text":"Identity politics divides us. Fiction connects."},{"time":883000,"text":"One is interested in sweeping generalizations."},{"time":886000,"text":"The other, in nuances."},{"time":888000,"text":"One draws boundaries."},{"time":890000,"text":"The other recognizes no frontiers."},{"time":892000,"text":"Identity politics is made of solid bricks."},{"time":895000,"text":"Fiction is flowing water."}]},{"cues":[{"time":898000,"text":"In the Ottoman times, there were itinerant storytellers called \"meddah.\""},{"time":901000,"text":"They would go to coffee houses,"},{"time":903000,"text":"where they would tell a story in front of an audience,"},{"time":905000,"text":"often improvising."},{"time":907000,"text":"With each new person in the story,"},{"time":909000,"text":"the meddah would change his voice,"},{"time":911000,"text":"impersonating that character."},{"time":913000,"text":"Everybody could go and listen, you know --"},{"time":915000,"text":"ordinary people, even the sultan, Muslims and non-Muslims."},{"time":918000,"text":"Stories cut across all boundaries,"},{"time":921000,"text":"like \"The Tales of Nasreddin Hodja,\""},{"time":923000,"text":"which were very popular throughout the Middle East,"},{"time":925000,"text":"North Africa, the Balkans and Asia."},{"time":928000,"text":"Today, stories continue"},{"time":930000,"text":"to transcend borders."},{"time":932000,"text":"When Palestinian and Israeli politicians talk,"},{"time":935000,"text":"they usually don't listen to each other,"},{"time":937000,"text":"but a Palestinian reader"},{"time":939000,"text":"still reads a novel by a Jewish author,"},{"time":941000,"text":"and vice versa, connecting and empathizing"},{"time":944000,"text":"with the narrator."},{"time":946000,"text":"Literature has to take us beyond."},{"time":948000,"text":"If it cannot take us there,"},{"time":950000,"text":"it is not good literature."}]},{"cues":[{"time":952000,"text":"Books have saved the introverted,"},{"time":954000,"text":"timid child that I was -- that I once was."},{"time":957000,"text":"But I'm also aware of the danger"},{"time":959000,"text":"of fetishizing them."},{"time":961000,"text":"When the poet and mystic, Rumi,"},{"time":963000,"text":"met his spiritual companion, Shams of Tabriz,"},{"time":966000,"text":"one of the first things the latter did"},{"time":968000,"text":"was to toss Rumi's books into water"},{"time":970000,"text":"and watch the letters dissolve."},{"time":972000,"text":"The Sufis say, \"Knowledge that takes you not beyond yourself"},{"time":976000,"text":"is far worse than ignorance.\""},{"time":979000,"text":"The problem with today's cultural ghettos"},{"time":981000,"text":"is not lack of knowledge --"},{"time":983000,"text":"we know a lot about each other, or so we think --"},{"time":986000,"text":"but knowledge that takes us not beyond ourselves:"},{"time":989000,"text":"it makes us elitist,"},{"time":991000,"text":"distant and disconnected."},{"time":993000,"text":"There's a metaphor which I love:"},{"time":995000,"text":"living like a drawing compass."},{"time":997000,"text":"As you know, one leg of the compass is static, rooted in a place."},{"time":1000000,"text":"Meanwhile, the other leg"},{"time":1002000,"text":"draws a wide circle, constantly moving."},{"time":1004000,"text":"Like that, my fiction as well."},{"time":1006000,"text":"One part of it is rooted in Istanbul,"},{"time":1008000,"text":"with strong Turkish roots,"},{"time":1011000,"text":"but the other part travels the world,"},{"time":1013000,"text":"connecting to different cultures."},{"time":1015000,"text":"In that sense, I like to think of my fiction"},{"time":1017000,"text":"as both local and universal,"},{"time":1020000,"text":"both from here and everywhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1022000,"text":"Now those of you who have been to Istanbul"},{"time":1024000,"text":"have probably seen Topkapi Palace,"},{"time":1026000,"text":"which was the residence of Ottoman sultans"},{"time":1028000,"text":"for more than 400 years."},{"time":1031000,"text":"In the palace, just outside the quarters"},{"time":1033000,"text":"of the favorite concubines,"},{"time":1035000,"text":"there's an area called The Gathering Place of the Djinn."},{"time":1038000,"text":"It's between buildings."},{"time":1040000,"text":"I'm intrigued by this concept."},{"time":1042000,"text":"We usually distrust those areas"},{"time":1044000,"text":"that fall in between things."},{"time":1046000,"text":"We see them as the domain"},{"time":1048000,"text":"of supernatural creatures like the djinn,"},{"time":1050000,"text":"who are made of smokeless fire"},{"time":1052000,"text":"and are the symbol of elusiveness."},{"time":1054000,"text":"But my point is perhaps"},{"time":1056000,"text":"that elusive space"},{"time":1058000,"text":"is what writers and artists need most."},{"time":1061000,"text":"When I write fiction"},{"time":1063000,"text":"I cherish elusiveness and changeability."},{"time":1065000,"text":"I like not knowing what will happen 10 pages later."},{"time":1068000,"text":"I like it when my characters surprise me."},{"time":1070000,"text":"I might write about"},{"time":1072000,"text":"a Muslim woman in one novel,"},{"time":1074000,"text":"and perhaps it will be a very happy story,"},{"time":1076000,"text":"and in my next book, I might write"},{"time":1078000,"text":"about a handsome, gay professor in Norway."},{"time":1081000,"text":"As long as it comes from our hearts,"},{"time":1083000,"text":"we can write about anything and everything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1086000,"text":"Audre Lorde once said,"},{"time":1088000,"text":"\"The white fathers taught us to say,"},{"time":1091000,"text":"'I think, therefore I am.'\""},{"time":1093000,"text":"She suggested, \"I feel, therefore I am free.\""},{"time":1096000,"text":"I think it was a wonderful paradigm shift."},{"time":1099000,"text":"And yet, why is it that,"},{"time":1101000,"text":"in creative writing courses today,"},{"time":1103000,"text":"the very first thing we teach students is"},{"time":1105000,"text":"\"write what you know\"?"},{"time":1107000,"text":"Perhaps that's not the right way to start at all."},{"time":1110000,"text":"Imaginative literature is not necessarily about"},{"time":1113000,"text":"writing who we are or what we know"},{"time":1116000,"text":"or what our identity is about."},{"time":1119000,"text":"We should teach young people and ourselves"},{"time":1121000,"text":"to expand our hearts"},{"time":1123000,"text":"and write what we can feel."},{"time":1125000,"text":"We should get out of our cultural ghetto"},{"time":1127000,"text":"and go visit the next one and the next."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1130000,"text":"In the end, stories move like whirling dervishes,"},{"time":1133000,"text":"drawing circles beyond circles."},{"time":1136000,"text":"They connect all humanity,"},{"time":1138000,"text":"regardless of identity politics,"},{"time":1140000,"text":"and that is the good news."},{"time":1142000,"text":"And I would like to finish with an old Sufi poem:"},{"time":1144000,"text":"\"Come, let us be friends for once;"},{"time":1147000,"text":"let us make life easy on us;"},{"time":1149000,"text":"let us be lovers and loved ones;"},{"time":1151000,"text":"the earth shall be left to no one.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":1154000,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":1156000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}